<!-- Pacific Strike CIA memorandum event, adapted from Strike Group Molniya U.S.-voice interstitial format. -->
<Page
  xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
  xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
  xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
  mc:Ignorable="d"
  d:DesignWidth="1920"
  d:DesignHeight="1080">
  <Viewbox>
    <Border Background="White" HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" Width="864" Height="1120" Padding="45"
            TextElement.FontFamily="Courier New" TextElement.Foreground="Black" TextElement.FontSize="16">
      <Border.Effect>
        <DropShadowEffect />
      </Border.Effect>

      <Border BorderThickness="0,10,10,10" BorderBrush="#FF000000">
        <Grid>
          <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="10"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
          </Grid.RowDefinitions>
          <TextBlock Text="C05084534" Background="#FFFFFFFF" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="17,-15,0,0" Padding="5,0,5,0" />
          <Grid Grid.Row="0">
            <Grid.RowDefinitions>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="10"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="15"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="15"/>
              <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            </Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
              <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
              <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
              <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
              <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
            </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="0" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" Text="TOP SECRET" TextAlignment="Center"/>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="0" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" Grid.RowSpan="2" TextAlignment="Center" FontFamily="Times New Roman">
              The Director of Central Intelligence
              <LineBreak/>
              <LineBreak/>
              <Run FontSize="12">Washington D.C., 20505</Run>
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="3" Text="21 September 1985"/>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="6" Grid.Column="3" Text="222X1"/>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="7" Grid.Column="0" Text="MEMORANDUM FOR:   "/>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="7" Grid.Column="1" TextWrapping="Wrap">
              JCS WASHINGTON DC//J3//
              <LineBreak/>
              USCINCPAC HONOLULU HI
              <LineBreak/>
              CINCPACFLT PEARL HARBOR HI
              <LineBreak/>
              COMUSPHIL MANILA PI
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="7" Grid.Column="3" TextWrapping="Wrap">
              EO 13526 3.3(b)(1)&gt;25Yrs
              <LineBreak/>
              EO 13526 3.5(c)
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="9" Grid.Column="0" Text="SUBJECT:   "/>
            <TextBlock Grid.Row="9" Grid.Column="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="3" Text="Chinese Command Traffic Following Sandakan Raid"/>
          </Grid>
          <TextBlock Grid.Row="2" TextWrapping="Wrap">
            1. Compartmented source STAR LIGHT at Puerto Princesa City has passed Chinese command traffic acknowledging failure of the Sandakan strike to destroy Allied amphibious staging forces. The traffic reflects urgent concern that Allied forces are now positioned to move against Palawan.
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
            2. PLA and PLAN channels direct Palawan commanders to hold Puerto Princesa and Quezon at all cost. Requests include additional coastal missile reloads, engineers, ammunition, mobile SAM systems, and shore-control detachments. Soviet support from Cam Ranh is requested for air cover and convoy escort.
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
            3. Expect the enemy to compensate by hardening Puerto Princesa, shifting reserves toward Quezon on the island's west coast, and using small craft, coastal missiles, and submarines to contest any landing.
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
			4. Intercepts report that the two Chinese commanders responsible for the failed strike on Sandakan have been called back to the mainland and our source believes they will be executed. We assess this will harden resolve of local commanders at Palawan as a response.
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
            5. Chinese and Soviet commanders appear to understand Palawan is exposed. Given this, we assess a rapid Allied move would likely precede the reinforcement channels now being requested.
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
          </TextBlock>
          <TextBlock TextAlignment="Right" Text="William J. Casey, Director" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="480,500,0,0" Grid.Row="2"/>
          <TextBlock Grid.Row="2" Grid.RowSpan="3" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">
            <Run TextDecorations="Underline">Distribution by ER/21 September 1985 w/Att</Run>
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
            Orig - Each Addressee
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - DCI
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - DDCI
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - EXDIR
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - C/NIC
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - VC/NIC
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - NIO/Warning
            <LineBreak/>
               1 - ER File
          </TextBlock>
          <TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Text="TOP SECRET" TextAlignment="Center"/>
        </Grid>
      </Border>
    </Border>
  </Viewbox>
</Page>
